race.comment: GODDESS OF ROCK (5) resumed in good order over 1400m and then closed too well to score in a CL3 over 1600m at Launceston. Has an awkward gate to manage but keeps the handy 3kg and with average luck she can go back-to-back. SKY EAGLE (11) has threatened all preparation and is back in grade. Byrne Burke is flying and she replaces the 3kg apprentice. Rates well and the mare will hit the line hard. Stablemate BAYBOUGG (1) improved again when placing at Launceston over 1400m. Has the benefit of a 3kg claim and she has won here over a mile. She's a chance to bounce. STEELE MY SUNSHINE (13) is a leader who has won here over the trip. Capable enough and she will get every chance from an inside gate.
